data.enText: built to be fixed into a particular space
with matching cupboards and other furniture built for the space and fixed in place
made to follow the shape of the body
suitable; with the right qualities and skills

data.chText: 她很适合演悲剧女主角。
data.enText: She was well fitted to the role of tragic heroine.

data.chText: 窗户有锁的房子保险费用降低。
data.enText: Insurance costs will be reduced for houses fitted with window locks.

means: (大小、式样、数量适合)可容纳，装进

tr: being the right size and shape to fit as desired
example: he quickly assembled the fitted pieces

value.def: A fitted piece of clothing is designed so that it is the same size and shape as your body rather than being loose.

example.tran: 宽松的裤子配上紧身夹克

value.def: A fitted piece of furniture, for example a cupboard, is designed to fill a particular space and is fixed in place.

example.ex: I've re-carpeted our bedroom and added fitted wardrobes.
example.tran: 我重铺了卧室的地毯，又添置了定做的壁橱。

value.def: A fitted carpet is cut to the same shape as a room so that it covers the floor completely.

example.ex: ...fitted carpets, central heating and double glazing.
example.tran: 定制的地毯、中央供暖和双层玻璃窗

value.tran: (地毯)铺满房间的，定做的，大小合适的

value.def: A fitted sheet has the corners sewn so that they fit over the corners of the mattress and do not have to be folded.
value.tran: (床单)大小合适的，按尺寸缝边的

value.def: A person who is fitted to do something or fitted for something has the right qualities for it.

example.ex: Helen was ill fitted to fulfil her daughter's ideal of a gentle mother-figure.
example.tran: 海伦与她女儿理想中的温柔母亲形象相差甚远。

value.tran: 合适的;有能力的;胜任的

value.def: If a room is fitted with objects, those objects are in the room and are normally fixed in place.

example.ex: Bedrooms are fitted with alarm pull cords to alert the manager in an emergency.
example.tran: 卧室中装有警报器拉绳，遇到紧急情况时可向经理报警。

trans: (铺满房间地板的)订做的地毯
